1. d4
d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. e4 b5 6. e5 Nd5 7. a4 e6 8. axb5 Bb4 9.
Qc2 {This is another way to try to transfer the queen to the kingside. However,
this will cost White too many tempi, allowing Black to create some serious
threats on the queenside} Nb6 10. Qe4 {The most logical idea. White is
transferring the queen to the kingside.} ({The move} 10. bxa6 {only helps
Black to complete the development of his pieces.} Nxa6 $5 11. Be2 (11. Qe4 $2
Nc5 $1 $17) 11... Bb7 $11 {and the white queen does not make it to the kingside
}) 10... Qd5 11. Qg4 axb5 12. Rxa8 Qxa8 13. Qxg7 (13. Be2 g6 $1 $15 {Delchev's
suggestion, which he evaluates as better for Black already. The following
lines seem to support his conclusion} 14. O-O (14. Ng5 h6 15. Nge4 Bb7 16. O-O
Bxc3 17. Nxc3 Bc6 18. h4 N8d7 19. Qg3 h5 20. Qg5 b4 $17) (14. Nd2 h5 15. Qg3 h4
16. Qg4 h3 17. Bf3 Bb7 18. Nde4 (18. Nxb5 Bxd2+ 19. Bxd2 Qa1+ $19) 18... Be7 {
[%cal Rh8h4] /\...Rh4} 19. Nxb5 Qa5+ 20. Nec3 Rh4 21. Qg3 Bxf3 22. Qxf3 hxg2
23. Qxg2 Nd5 24. O-O Nxc3 25. Nxc3 Rxd4 $17) 14... Bxc3 15. bxc3 h6 16. Qh3 Qa2
(16... Qe4 $5) (16... Bb7 $5) 17. Bd1 Qb1 18. Bg5 Qf5 $17 {0-1 (31) Gormally,D
(2504)-Edouard,R (2632) England 2016}) 13... Qa1 $1 14. Qxh8+ Kd7 15. Kd1 Na4
$5 $146 {Objectively speaking, the engine evaluates this position as equal.
However, the moves that White must find to keep the game balanced are
literally inhuman} (15... Bxc3 16. bxc3 Qa4+ (16... Nd5 $6 17. Qxh7 Nxc3+ 18.
Kd2 Nc6 19. Qxf7+ $1 (19. Qc2 $6 Na4 $44 {0-1 (33) Komarov,D (2539)-Fominyh,A 
(2571) Cairo 2001}) 19... Ne7 20. Qh7 (20. Ng5 $5) 20... Qa2+ 21. Ke1 (21. Kxc3
b4+ 22. Kxb4 Qb3+ 23. Kc5 Ba6 $19) 21... Bb7 22. Nd2 Qa1 23. Qc2 $18) 17. Ke1
Qa1 $11) 16. Nd5 {is the computer's top choice!} ({Bad is} 16. Qxh7 $2 Nxb2+
17. Ke2 Qxc1 18. Qxf7+ Kc6 $17) ({An alternative is} 16. Bxc4 $5 {when after}
Nxb2+ 17. Ke2 Nxc4 18. Ne4 Qa2+ 19. Bd2 Bxd2 20. Nfxd2 Nxd2 21. Nxd2 Nc6 22.
Qxh7 Nxd4+ 23. Ke3 Nf5+ 24. Ke2 Nd4+ $11 {the game ends with a perpetual.})
16... Nxb2+ (16... exd5 17. e6+ $18) 17. Ke2 Qxc1 18. Nf6+ Kc6 19. Qxc8 Nd3 20.
g3 Qc2+ 21. Ke3 Qc1+ $11 *

