{Do you remember what was the key idea for Black in this position?} 5... Nd7 $1
{In the 5.Nc3 line it was important for the knight to go to d5 since it gave
Black the additional option of playing ...Ndb4. Here the knight must go to d7 
since this will give Black the option of playing the ...e5 pawn break. These
two factors (...Nb4 and ...e5) are the subtleties that will determine whether.
..Nd7 or ...Nd5 is called for. However, if the knight is headed to b6 then it
won't make a difference} *

